h3. Problem

The image path lost his reference after doing a require and export.

h3. Reproducible steps:
 
1. Run the attached code with 1.8.0.1 Titanium SDK.
Please see the 1.8.0.1 attached image.

2. Run the attached code with 1.7.5 Titanium SDK.
Please see the 1.7.5 attached image.

Notice that in 1.7.5 Titanium SDK the all images are displayed well on the first window.

h3. Expected behavior:
Customer wants to have the same behavior in 1.8.0.1 Titanium SDK like the 1.7.5 attached image.

h3. More info:

The images are displayed well in 1.7.5 Titanium SDK.


h3. Tested with the next specs:

Simulator
Android version : 2.3.3

iPhone 4
Version of the device: 5.0.1

Titanium Studio, build: 1.0.8.201112291658
Titanium SDK: 1.8.0.1 & 1.7.5

Samsung Fit

tested on:

Titanium SDK version: 3.1.0

Android Emulator: Android SDK version: 2.2
iOS iPhone Simulator: iOS SDK version: 6.0

Turns out the Android behavior is correct and the iOS behavior is not. I created TIMOB-23809 to fix it for iOS. No idea about Windows.
